d its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Willington was born about 1449, in Todenham, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Willington, was 74 and his mother, Mrs Margery Willington, was 71. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Ann Littleton. He died on 31 January 1500, at the age of 52."},"et":{"ABT 1449–22 Jan 1500 will dated":"umbes 1449–31. jaanuar 1500","1449–1500":"1449–1500","1418–1454":"1418–1454","1440–Female":"1440–Surnud","1460–1512":"1460–1512","1465–Male":"1465–Surnud","1429–Male":"1429–Surnud","1432–1454":"1432–1454","1377–Male":"1377–Surnud","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","22 Jan 1500 will dated":"31. jaanuar 1500","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","ABT 1449":"umbes 1449","1380":"1380","1448":"1448","1512":"1512","1500":"1500","1454":"1454","1377":"1377","1432":"1432","1465":"1465","WILL DATED 22 JAN 1500":"31. jaanuar 1500","about 1465":"umbes 1465","22 JAN 1500":"31. jaanuar 1500","1418":"1418","1429":"1429","1449":"1449","Todenham, Gloucestershire, England":"Todenham, Gloucestershire, England","England":"England","Of, Todenham, Gloucestershire, England":"Todenham, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1449–22 Jan 1500 will dated":"noin 1449–31. tammikuuta 1500","1449–1500":"1449–1500","1418–1454":"1418–1454","1440–Female":"1440–Kuollut","1460–1512":"1460–1512","1465–Male":"1465–Kuollut","1429–Male":"1429–Kuollut","1432–1454":"1432–1454","1377–Male":"1377–Kuollut","1380–Female":"1380–Kuollut","22 Jan 1500 will dated":"31. tammikuuta 1500","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","ABT 1449":"noin 1449","1380":"1380","1448":"1448","1512":"1512","1500":"1500","1454":"1454","1377":"1377","1432":"1432","1465":"1465"